  <description type="morphology">Fruiting specimens of var. convoluta with characteristic perichaetial leaves are
        not uncommon in the far West, and are often robust in stature. The Illinois record is from
        J. A. McCleary and P. L. Redfearn Jr. (1979). Many collections cited from Florida are
        actually Barbula indica.</description>
